      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Stallings Park & Stevens Mill — Aging Pipes in Pre-2000 Homes' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Stallings Park dates back to 1971, and Stevens Mill was built in 1994. Many of these homes still run on original copper or galvanized steel plumbing that corrodes from the inside over time. We see burst pipes, slow slab leaks, and water heater failures in this area regularly. Rusty water when you first turn on the faucet is the warning sign. If a pipe lets go, shut off your main valve and call us at <a href="tel:9802773700">980-277-3700</a> — we can be there in under 45 minutes.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Stonewood & Wendover at Curry Place — Early CPVC Failures' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Stonewood was built between 1998 and 1999, and Wendover at Curry Place went up around 2006. Homes in this age range often used early CPVC supply lines that get brittle over time and crack at the fittings. We get calls from these neighborhoods for supply line failures behind walls that went unnoticed for days. If you notice low water pressure, a warm spot on a wall, or a spike in your water bill, call us before the damage spreads into your subfloor.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Crooked Creek Watershed — Storm Flooding' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'The Crooked Creek watershed runs through the middle of Stallings. Homes that back up to the creek and its tributaries face the highest risk during heavy rain. The town\'s stormwater department has documented problems with erosion, sinkholes, and flooding along natural drainage paths. We respond to <a href="/storm-damage">storm and flood damage calls</a> in these areas with truck-mounted pumps that can remove thousands of gallons per hour.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Vickery, Sterling Manor & Southstone — New Construction Defects' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Vickery, Sterling Manor, and Southstone were all built after 2016. The plumbing is new, but construction defects still cause water damage. Improperly sealed shower pans, loose water heater connections, and bad grading around the foundation are the most common problems we find in newer Stallings homes. Because these houses look new, many owners don\'t expect a water event — and by the time they notice a problem, mold has already started behind the walls.' },
      { tag: 'h2', html: 'We Handle Your Insurance — You Handle Your Family' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Dealing with water damage is stressful enough without fighting your insurance company. We use Xactimate, the same estimating software your adjuster uses, so your claim moves fast with no surprises.' }
