    h1: 'Weddington\'s Trusted 24/7 Water Damage Restoration Team',
    metaDescription: '24/7 water damage restoration in Weddington, NC. 25-35 min response. IICRC certified. Water removal, structural drying, mold prevention & rebuild. Call now.',
    heroTag: '🚨 24/7 Emergency Dispatch — Weddington', heroSub: 'Crews on the ground in 25-35 minutes across Weddington, Waxhaw, and southern Union County. We handle the water removal, structural drying, mold prevention, and full rebuild — start to finish with one dedicated project manager. Direct insurance billing through Xactimate.', heroTrust: ['Top-Rated in Weddington', '25-35 Min Response', 'Licensed, Insured & IICRC', 'Direct Insurance Billing'],
    body: [
      { tag: 'h2', html: '24/7 Water Damage Restoration in Weddington, NC' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Water spreading through your home and you don\'t know where to start? Call <a href="tel:9802773700">980-277-3700</a>. We\'re Carolina Pro Restoration, and our crew can be at your door in Weddington in about 25 to 35 minutes. We show up with truck-mounted extractors, commercial dehumidifiers, and FLIR thermal imaging cameras — everything needed to stop the damage and start drying your home the same hour you call.' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Weddington is a growing town of about 14,400 residents in southern Union County, North Carolina, about 13 miles from our Fort Mill headquarters. The area gets around 44 inches of rain per year, and 7.9% of properties face flood risk over the next 30 years according to First Street Foundation data. The East Fork of Twelvemile Creek cuts through residential areas across Weddington, creating flooding pressure on homes built near low-lying land. We handle burst pipes, water heater failures, washing machine overflows, toilet supply line breaks, <a href="/sewage-cleanup">sewage backups</a>, and storm flooding throughout Weddington and nearby <a href="/water-damage-restoration-waxhaw-nc">Waxhaw</a>, <a href="/water-damage-restoration-indian-land-sc">Indian Land</a>, and <a href="/water-damage-restoration-charlotte-nc">Charlotte</a>.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Why Weddington Homes Are at Risk' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Weddington\'s housing stock is mostly from the late 1990s through the 2010s, with a median build year around 1998. Older neighborhoods like Weddington Heights and Longview used early CPVC supply lines that get brittle over time and crack without warning — especially in unconditioned attics and crawl spaces. Newer luxury subdivisions like Bromley, Atherton, and The Falls at Weddington have homes worth over $1 million with high-end finishes where every hour of unchecked water drives up repair costs fast. Builder-grade water heater connections and appliance fittings in these homes are now entering their first failure window.' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Weddington also sits on Union County\'s red-clay soil, which holds water against foundations instead of draining it away. The East Fork of Twelvemile Creek runs through town and has a documented history of flooding nearby homes during heavy storms. Hurricane Helene in 2024 saturated the region and overwhelmed storm drains across southern Union County.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'What Happens When You Call Us' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Our IICRC-certified crew arrives fast, maps every wet area using thermal cameras and moisture meters, extracts standing water with commercial-grade equipment, and sets up a full drying system with dehumidifiers and air movers. We treat affected surfaces with antimicrobial solution to prevent <a href="/mold-removal">mold growth</a> before it starts. Every step is documented with photos and moisture readings from day one.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Insurance & Xactimate Documentation' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'We write every estimate in Xactimate — the same software your insurance adjuster uses. That means no surprises, no back-and-forth, and no delays on your claim. We take the damage photos, send daily moisture reports, communicate directly with your adjuster, and bill your insurance company so you pay nothing out of pocket for covered work.' },
      { tag: 'h2', html: 'Common Water Damage Problems in Weddington Neighborhoods' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Weddington Heights & Longview — Brittle CPVC Supply Lines' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Weddington Heights and Longview were built between 1999 and 2008. Many of these homes used early CPVC supply lines that get brittle with age, especially in attics and crawl spaces that aren\'t heated or cooled. We get calls from these neighborhoods for supply line cracks behind bathroom walls and under kitchen sinks that dump hundreds of gallons before anyone notices. If you see a drop in water pressure or a damp spot on a wall, call us at <a href="tel:9802773700">980-277-3700</a> before the damage spreads into the subfloor.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Highgate & Weddington Chase — Sewer Lateral Root Intrusion' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Highgate and Weddington Chase are estate-lot communities built between 2000 and 2006 with mature trees throughout. Those mature roots grow into sewer laterals over time. A slow drain turns into a full <a href="/sewage-cleanup">sewage backup</a> without warning. That means contaminated water on your floors — what the industry calls a Category 3 event. We scope the lateral, extract the water, treat with antimicrobials, and rebuild whatever needs to come out. One call handles the whole thing.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Twelvemile Creek Flood Zone — Storm Drainage Overflow' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'The East Fork of Twelvemile Creek runs through Weddington and has flooded nearby homes during heavy storms. When back-to-back thunderstorms or tropical remnants dump rain faster than the creek can handle, water pushes into crawl spaces, garages, and ground-level rooms. We respond with truck-mounted pumps that can pull thousands of gallons per hour and set up commercial drying systems the same day. If you live near the creek and see water pooling in your yard after a storm, don\'t wait — call us before it gets inside.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Bromley, Atherton & The Falls at Weddington — New Construction Defects' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'These newer luxury communities were built from 2013 to now. Homes here run over $1 million with hardwood floors, custom tile, and finished basements. New doesn\'t mean safe. We see problems with grading that sends stormwater toward the foundation instead of away from it, HVAC condensate lines that weren\'t sealed right, and dishwasher and ice-maker connections that loosen within a few years. Our thermal cameras find moisture behind brand-new drywall without cutting holes.' },
      { tag: 'h2', html: 'We Handle Your Insurance — You Handle Your Family' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Dealing with water damage is stressful enough without fighting your insurance company. We use Xactimate, the same estimating software your adjuster uses, so your claim moves fast with no surprises.' }
    ],
