      { tag: 'h2', html: 'Common Water Damage Problems in Indian Trail Neighborhoods' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Sun Valley & Hemby Acres — Aging Supply Lines' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Sun Valley and Hemby Acres were built between 1997 and 2003. Many of these homes used polybutylene or early CPVC supply lines that break down from the inside after 15 to 20 years. We get calls from these neighborhoods regularly for leaks behind drywall that went unnoticed for days or weeks. If you see a drop in water pressure, a warm spot on a wall, or a spike in your water bill, call us at <a href="tel:9802773700">980-277-3700</a> before the damage spreads into your subfloor.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Hemby Bridge & Country Woods — Crawlspace Moisture' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Homes in Hemby Bridge and Country Woods sit on larger lots along the eastern side of town. Most are built on crawlspace foundations over Union County\'s heavy clay soil. After a storm, that clay holds water against the foundation for days. We regularly pull wet insulation and treat mold growth in crawlspaces throughout these neighborhoods. If you smell something musty or damp when you walk through your front door, there\'s a good chance moisture is building underneath. Our team uses thermal imaging to check without tearing anything out.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Goose Creek & Crooked Creek Watershed — Storm Flooding' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'The Goose Creek and Crooked Creek watersheds run through Indian Trail and cover nearly 100 square miles combined. Homes that back up to these creeks face the highest risk. NOAA flood gauges along Goose Creek have recorded multiple flood-stage events that sent water into yards, garages, and ground-level rooms. We respond to <a href="/storm-damage">storm and flood damage calls</a> in these areas with truck-mounted pumps that can remove thousands of gallons per hour.' },
      { tag: 'h3', html: 'Brookhaven & Newer Subdivisions — Construction Defects' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Indian Trail added thousands of homes after 2010. The plumbing in these houses is newer, but construction defects still cause water damage. Improperly sealed shower pans, loose water heater connections, and bad grading around the foundation are the most common problems we find. Because these homes are still under warranty or recently out of it, many owners don\'t expect a water event — and by the time they notice a problem, mold has already started behind the walls. We use thermal cameras and moisture meters to find hidden moisture before it spreads.' },
      { tag: 'h2', html: 'We Handle Your Insurance — You Handle Your Family' },
      { tag: 'p', html: 'Dealing with water damage is stressful enough without fighting your insurance company. We use Xactimate, the same estimating software your adjuster uses, so your claim moves fast with no surprises.' }
